HEADWORD: Hercogamous
<hw>Her*cog"a*mous</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/ a
fence + <?/ marriage.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>Not capable of
self-fertilization; -- said of hermaphrodite flowers in which some
structural obstacle forbids autogamy.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

